laboratory_examinations.findings: Round lesion with sclerotic and regular margins in the lower zone of the left lung, adjacent to the lower pole of the scapula.

Round-shaped accessory ossicle with a 2 cm diameter, corticated and smooth contours, located at the anterior part of the inferior angle of the left scapula. Mild elevation of the left shoulder classified as Grade 1 Sprengel deformity.
